*** NOTE: Tested with GNU 4.7.2.

To use the GOMP wrapper, do the following:

WITH PDT INSTRUMENTATION:
------------------------

- configure and build tau with: -openmp -pdt=<path-to-pdt>
- cd examples/gomp_wrapper (this directory)
- make
- tau_exec -T pdt,openmp,serial -v -loadlib=./libgomp_g_wrapper/libgomp_g_wrap.so ./matmult

WITHOUT PDT INSTRUMENTATION:
---------------------------

- configure and build tau with: -openmp -bfd=download -unwind_inc=<path-to-libunwind>/include -unwind_lib=<path-to-libunwind>/lib -unwinder=libunwind
- cd examples/gomp_wrapper (this directory)
- make
- cd libgomp_g_wrapper
- make
- cd ..
- tau_exec -T pdt,openmp,serial -v -loadlib=./libgomp_g_wrapper/libgomp_g_wrap.so ./matmult

NOTES:
-----

You may also have to:
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:<path-to-libunwind>/lib:<path-to-tau>/examples/gomp/libgomp_g_wrapper:<path-to-tau>/<arch>/lib

If you prefer, you can link in the wrapper rather than preload it. See the Makefile for details.
